This is a human-readable summary of the AGPL v3 license. It is not a substitute for the full license text.

Permissions (What you CAN do)

Commercial Use: You can use this software for commercial purposes.
Modification: You can modify the software.
Distribution: You can distribute copies of the software.
Private Use: You can use and modify the software for private purposes without any obligation to release the source code.
Patent Grant: You are granted a license to any patents held by the contributors that are necessary to use the software.

Conditions (What you MUST do)

Disclose Source: You must make the source code available when you distribute the software.
Network Use is Distribution: If you run a modified version of this software on a server and let users interact with it over a network, you must provide them with a way to get the source code of your modified version. This is the key feature of the AGPL.
License and Copyright Notice: You must include the original copyright notice and a copy of the AGPL v3 license with the software.
State Changes: You must document any significant changes you make to the source code.
Same License (Copyleft): Any modifications you make and distribute must be licensed under the AGPL v3 as well.

Limitations (What you CANNOT do & Disclaimers)

No Warranty: The software is provided "as is" without any warranty.
No Liability: The authors or copyright holders cannot be held liable for any damages.
No Sublicensing: You may not sublicense the work under any other license.
Trademark Use: This license does not grant you any rights to use the trademarks, service marks, or names of the contributors.
